{"key":"post-19519395","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>19519395</id>\n<content>1.&amp;nbsp; Never cover the holes in a shotgun terrarium with anything.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;2.&amp;nbsp; Those type of ants are extremely easy to get rid of.&amp;nbsp; Simply put a jar lid with karo syrup or sugar water, with a spoon of 20 mule team borax stirred into it.&amp;nbsp; The ants will eat the sugar water and carry the borax back to their nest.&amp;nbsp; Borax is toxic to sugar eating ants, but it takes about a week to kill them.&amp;nbsp; During that time, they'll take load after load of borax/sugar water back to the nest where they feed it to the larvae and queen, killing the whole nest.</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>19519123</prev>\n<first>19518466</first>\n<last>19519395</last>\n<when>1391522332</when>\n<utime>02/04/14 03:58 PM</utime>\n</post>"}